HEADWORD: cased
<hw>cased</hw> <pos>adj.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>covered or protected
with or as if with a case; <as>as, knights <ex>cased</ex> in
steel</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> encased, incased.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>same as <er>bound</er>; -- of books.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> covered.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

<p><ent>caseful</ent>⟦br⟧
